	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=21002&amp;mid=10746704811836">re: focii Stacking</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=21002&amp;mid=10746704811836#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Wed, Jan 21st 2:34 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=187635"><span id=" ">LokabbCIC</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">3 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Generally - items of the same TYPE -( ie: Mana pres,&nbsp;&nbsp; Spell Haste, Imprv Dmg.) will NOT stack with each other -- the Single Highest  bonus will apply..   Fury of Ro &amp; Fury of Ec'i will both work, but ONLY on the spcific spells to which they apply ( Ro on ONLY Fire, and EC'i on ONLY Ice based spells), and ID4 will not add ontop of these either, as Fury has a higher % than the normal ID Effect. ( which is +20%, for ID4)  - same goes for mana pres..  if you have 1 effect that gives -20% mana used, and one that gives -35% mana used. ONLY the -35% will take effect.  <br/><br/>  as said above - the Focii Effects WILL stack with SOME buffs. - ie Bard song, for ID,  -- Cleric spell haste buffs with Spell Haste focus.<br/><br/>Cinadien Farslayer - Wizard of the lands of Fironia Vie</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
